PRIVACY POLICY — BRIK
Last updated: April 3, 2026

Overview
BRIK is a personal fitness app designed to generate and track workouts on your device. Your privacy is important to us. This policy explains what data we collect (spoiler: none) and how your information is handled.

Data Collection
We do not collect any personal data. We do not require account creation, login, email addresses, or any personally identifiable information to use the app.

Local Storage Only
All workout data is stored locally on your device using on-device storage (AsyncStorage). Your equipment preferences, workout history, achievements, and settings never leave your phone. There are no servers receiving your data.

Analytics & Tracking
We do not use analytics, tracking pixels, advertising identifiers, or any form of usage monitoring. Your activity within the app is completely private.

Third-Party Sharing
We do not share, sell, rent, or transfer any data to third parties. Since we don't collect data, there is nothing to share.

Data Stored on Your Device
The only data stored is:
• Equipment preferences (which gear you own)
• Workout history (completed sessions)
• Achievement progress
• App settings (fitness level, duration, days per week)
All of this is stored locally on your device and is never transmitted anywhere.

Deleting Your Data
Since all data is stored locally on your device, you can delete all app data by simply uninstalling the app. There is no account to delete and no server-side data to request removal of.

Children's Privacy
We do not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under the age of 13.

Changes to This Policy
We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the app with an updated "Last Updated" date.

Contact
If you have any questions, please contact us at the email provided on our app store listing.
